title: Recall Notification Report
summary: WASHINGTON, Feb. 25, 2011 - J&J Distributing, a St. Paul, Minn., establishment, is recalling approximately 87 pounds of buffalo chicken cheese dip products because they contain monosodium glutamate (MSG) which is not declared on the label. The products subject to recall include: 16-oz. metal containers...
impacted_products: 16-oz. metal containers of "CUB FRESH BUFFALO CHICKEN CHEESE DIP."
16-oz. metal containers of "KOWALSKI'S MARKETS PLACE BUFFALO CHICKEN CHEESE DIP."
